    "summary": "Multi-disciplinary experience designer and art director for clients, such as Nike, Botter Paris, Van Moof, Lowlands Festival, the Rijksmuseum, STRP festival, Red Bull Music.\n\nBy combining my in-depth experiential experience, and top-level understanding of multiple creative technology platforms and in-depth 3D experience, I deliver engaging immersive concepts and provide creative direction for resonating end-to-end experience journeys for agencies, brands, and artists.\n\nWith an artist approach, deep knowledge of the production process, and an engineer\u2019s brain, I solve complex problems and I am able to push the boundaries of the creative within the aims and needs of each project, resulting in a cutting-edge body of work.\n\nLove working in tight-knit teams with great enthusiasm. Known to be involved and engaged with the team I am part of and projects I am working on. \n\nMy ultimate goal in every project is to let visitors be in awe, put their devices down, immerse themselves in the moment and let them leave with an altered perspective.",
